    dc:creator "Eya, Bryan K." ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Revision of the Genus Crioprosopus Audinet-Serville, and description of three new genera of Trachyderini (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae: Cerambycinae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.242649> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.242649>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11 – 18. Comparison of structural characters of Callistochroma and Crioprosopus: Callistochroma lampros: 11: prothoracic sculpture (male), 11 a: punctures confined to anterior angle; 12: prothoracic sculpture (female), 12 a: side of apical half of prothroax obtusely tuberculate; 13: prosternal and mesosternal intercoxal process, 13 a: mesosternal process obtusely tuberculate, extending below 13 b, 13 b: plane of prosternal intercoxal process; 14: elytral apices obliquely angulate, 14 a: outer armature. Crioprosopus basileus: 15: prothoracic sculpture (male), 15 a: disc densely punctate throughout; 16: prothoracic sculpture (female); 17: prosternal and mesosternal intercoxal process; 18: elytral apices rounded or subtruncate." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/242649/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

